{"id":"int-32e491b5","kind":"field_change","created_at":"2026-07-04T17:54:33.957023719Z","actor":"Nick Williams","issue_id":"prexu-jphh","extra":{"field":"status","new_value":"closed","old_value":"open","reason":"Resolved as hypothesis (b): mute is per-session BY DESIGN (bd memory player-mute-scope-decision) — kept across in-session episode handoff/autoplay, deliberately lost on stop. PR #38 (persistence) was wrong and reverted by PR #39, which documents the decision in code and pins the per-session reset with a regression test. In-mount handoff retention already worked and is covered by reveal-mute test (a). No behavior bug remains."}}
{"id":"int-ef295a96","kind":"field_change","created_at":"2026-07-04T18:11:35.471318514Z","actor":"Nick Williams","issue_id":"prexu-hg1j","extra":{"field":"status","new_value":"closed","old_value":"open","reason":"Fixed in PR #40: Linux skips the three WebView2-motivated staging mechanisms — busy-window class drop + 2xrAF ready deferral (useTransparentWindow), wait-for-IPC restore flip (PlayerContext), and the early opaque paint on exit (prepareNavAway). Windows/HTML5 unchanged. On-hardware verify steps in issue comment; if residual delay remains, instrument player_unload IPC duration next."}}
